						               													<description>Be a market vendor in Bansan, a lively game inspired by the  multisensory experience of a bustling wet market in Penang. You'll need to &amp;quot;bao ka liao&amp;quot;&amp;mdash;deal with fellow vendors, wholesalers, and customers; buy and sell ingredients; cook and serve hawker stall fare; keep the waste bins from overflowing; and navigate a myriad of events that changes up every game you play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player is a vendor renting market stalls while running a hawker food business in a bansan. On your turn, you will stock produce from the wholesale supply into market stalls, then take 2 actions from 3 options:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     BUY produce from other vendors or your wholesaler&amp;#10;     SELL produce to online customers&amp;#10;     EMPTY a waste bin &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Just like in local Asian markets, bargain at anytime to negotiate the best deals from other vendors. Then complete shopping lists of ingredients to make a variety of hawker food for your customers. The vendor who has earned the most money at game end wins!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There's also the Sendiri Mode - a solo way to play Bansan, and the Kenduri Mode - when the market gets a big order to host a feast!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Juggle the multiple roles of a vendor to win the title of &amp;quot;Bos Bansan!&amp;quot; Even if you get out-vended, you are guaranteed a taste of the chaos and excitement of local market culture in Malaysia!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
